				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">just have a metasprite x,y<br />based on the metasprite's x,y<br />automatic calculations can be performed to derive the proper relative x/y coordinates of the sub-sprites.<br /><br />For instance, in your 16x32 example, composed of 2 16x16 sprites.. call em sprite0 and sprite 1 in this example<br />metasprite x,y , call em mx,my<br />thus,<br />sprite0 x,y = (mx,my)<br />sprite1 x,y = (mx,my + 16)<br /><br />metasprite's x,y is the &quot;controller&quot; coordinates which the subsprite coords are derived from.  It's easy <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
